##Sister, are there enough sanitary pads and safety pants for the front line? East noon

Sister, are there enough sanitary pads and safety pants for the front line?

By Pandi

1

On the evening of February 6, Liang Yu scoured his micro blog and saw the news that doctors and nurses in the affected areas did not eat for hours and tried not to go to the toilet in order to save on protective clothing, a question immediately arose: "What about when they get their period? " And women made up a large proportion of the front-line staff. So she asked on Weibo: "Are there enough sanitary pads and Koalas for the frontline medical staff? "

The Post has been retweeted more than 200 times, which is not much compared to many topics related to the epidemic, but the comments section has been very active, and many people have expressed their understanding of her concerns, the practicability of feminine articles such as Tampons, Menstrual Cups and short-acting contraceptives in epidemic areas was also seriously discussed.

The next day, Liang Yu put the hashtag # sisterhood war epidemic relief action # on Weibo, appealing to netizens to pay attention to the issue of first-line Women's Menstrual Cycle. At the same time, she looked up information from the health commission's website and called several hospitals in Hubei to inquire about their needs. At the time, she just wanted to make a personal donation with a few friends. They want to donate safety pants, a feminine product that combines disposable underwear with sanitary Napkins and lasts longer than sanitary napkins. Koalas are one of them.

But things quickly went beyond Liang's expectations. On Feb. 7, she was approached by more than one brand and sent private messages from health care workers across the country. Some doctors at a designated hospital in Huanggang called for help for 160 women who could not leave the quarantine zone, "and the leaders have applied for help, but it has not been implemented. " Some people asked for safety pants on behalf of their friends at the shelter hospital, also asked if Liang Yu can help buy short-sleeved long johns, "they go out even have no time to change clothes with, to bare arms. "

There were so many people to contact and consult that Ms. Liang slept for 11 hours from Feb. 7 to 11 and spent her waking hours communicating with front-line health care providers, hospital officials and various interested companies. "At least a hundred people, " she estimated. The progress of the donation was also beyond her imagination. From the day of February 7 to the night of February 9, Liang Yu and her friends jointly led a targeted donation of more than 710,000 yuan in supplies and more than 110,000 pairs of safety pants, covering 20 hospitals in Wuhan, Huanggang and Xiaogan.

After she started collecting donations, Liang found out how big a gap there was in the supplies for women in the affected areas.

"My colleague's blood and urine are mixed together today. It's too hard. "

This is a private micro blog message that she received on the evening of February 11. A nurse from the Hainan Volunteer Team of Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital asked for comfort pants for two colleagues who were having their periods. Early in the morning of February 12, Liang Yu finally found a volunteer flute in Wuhan. At that time, the community had been sealed off and no one was allowed to enter. Early in the morning, the flute went over the wall and out of the community. It took a whole half day to find the materials and bought them and sent them to the shelter hospital.

Liang Yu, 24, has about 270,000 followers on her personal microblog@liang Yu Stacey. In the past few years, she has taken part in discussions on various gender issues on Weibo, engaging in lively debates with male chauvinist netizens and WWE The Great American Bash sexist comments. After the outbreak, she also several times with # see female workers # topic of the first-line Medical News, called on the media to "men and women soldiers" give "equal respect and coverage.

"I think it's a natural thing for men to be concerned about their rights, " Ms. Liang told me by phone. It was 11 p.m. , and she had just finished a meeting with her volunteer team to discuss optimizing the process. Her voice was Hoarse. But she's energetic, she talks fast, "I was educated as a child and naturally knew that I should be protected, but this society doesn't seem to follow the law very much. But it seems that men don't care and no one will violate their rights and interests, which makes me very confused,"said Liang.

The growing interest in the sister war relief initiative has led to questions: from those who feel that women's health supplies are not the most urgently needed in the affected areas to those who need to think about national priorities, to those who point out that her motives are not pure; Others say she spends too much on the Internet, suggesting that she might as well spend the money herself and let first-line doctors shop at the supermarket.

On Weibo, Liang revealed several moments of intense emotion. Once, on February 9, she offered to donate to the hospital. The other side said, "we are actually in urgent need of professional protective equipment. This is not urgent. " Two days later, she received a request for help from the hospital's front-line female doctors, at the same time learned that there are about 1,300 female health care workers. Another time, a doctor asked for help and replied, "let's triple the number of sanitary napkins. We never give them out. ". She could not understand why women's needs were so ignored. "Please see the female workers! " Liang Yu shouted on Weibo, the text of the anger.

But in the interview, Ms. Liang told me calmly that most of the time, she didn't have the energy to pay attention. A friend who volunteers to do psychological counseling for frontline doctors told Liang Yu that she was devastated to hear from a young woman who had just started her job and had been sent to the front line. Liang Yu and friends explained to each other: "contrast, we are just at home to knock the keyboard, we also want to try a little bit, their tolerance, adjust the past. "

However, one night, no time to sleep Liang Yu really too much pressure, according to the Internet a university of Psychological Counseling Center call, crying for an hour. "(No. 7) I felt that I couldn't do it. I really didn't sleep much. The information was overloaded and I had to deal with forms. But I hadn't sorted out the situation myself and didn't recruit people in time, " Liang told me. When she finished crying and hung up, she thought she was ready to fight again.

By February 10, Liang was finally overwhelmed and decided to recruit a team of volunteers.
On February 11, Hengan group donated women's articles to Hanchuan People's Hospital of Hubei Province through the "sister war epidemic relief operation" .
On February 12, Liang Yu donated 60 pairs of safety pants and 36 pairs of disposable underwear to the Hainan medical team of Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital.

2

Xiaoyong is one of the earliest volunteers of "peace of mind" . By the afternoon of Feb. 7, when she visited Liang's microblog, Xiaogan was already the city with the worst outbreak outside Wuhan. Although Xiaoyong is in the northeast, she thought of having three friends in Xiaogan, and she had been worried about them. So she sent a private message to Liang, saying that she could help coordinate the transportation of Xiaogan and communicate with the hospital.

Xiaoyong entered a wechat group of first-line doctors and nurses from Xiaogan hospitals, asked and sorted out their needs and sent them to Liang Yu, who contacted donations and logistics. For a day or two, she watched as the doctors and nurses from Xiaogan's prefectures and cities came in, their numbers rising from 30 or 40 to nearly 100. She made a total of three statistics on the material needs of Xiaogan women's medical care. On February 7, the first batch of statistics on the 8 designated hospitals with fever clinics, there were 5,900 female medical care workers on duty, reporting a total of 29,500 pairs of reassuring pants, the average person has only five, two a day, not enough for three days.

"people in many hospitals are embarrassed to ask for it. Some hospitals have more than 700 women on the job and say, 'just donate 500 pairs of safety pants, ' " Xiao said.

On Feb. 10, after Liang Yu posted a message asking for volunteers, private messages poured in. She said she had tens of thousands of unread messages on her microblog and could only "see fate" by clicking on them, and she was only vaguely aware, we need someone with a background in social work, media, statistics, management. On the same day, the volunteer team was divided according to function into a cargo group, fund-raising Group, docking group, Information Group, logistics group, Media Group, Publicity Group. By February 14, the team had 46 volunteers.

Doris, who was studying in graduate school, felt that it was meaningful for her to check Liang Yu's micro blog on Feb. 10 because of the delayed start of the school year. That night, along with five other volunteers, her personal wechat Qr code was placed in a poster created by the publicity team to show the progress of the fund-raising campaign. Between 7 a.m. and 10 p.m. on the 11th, Doris barely left her desk, connecting with more than 100 people, including the media, individual and group donations, medical help, and convoy volunteers. By the time she went to bed, it was well after 4 a.m. on the 12th.

Doris, who has prior experience as a volunteer volunteer, was brief and clear about her job responsibilities. She said that the focus of the docking team is to inquire, receive and verify the needs of local hospitals in Hubei Province for women's health supplies. Every day, Doris works with nearly 10 volunteers to create and update a detailed form (including hospital addresses, number of care providers, contact information, comfort pants sizes, etc.) that is verified and matched with donor supplies.

After a few days of donations, Ms. Liang said, they no longer had to actively solicit and collect information, and by Feb. 12, more than 140 hospitals had reached out to the team for help via private messages on Weibo or the docking group Wechat. Doris remembered coming to Huazhong University of Science and Technology for help three times in two days.

The information group is responsible for the docking group, the Logistics Group, fund-raising group to verify the information, input the form, and then together with the collection of donations, docking with the hospital, the use of donations, etc. . Starting at 8:00 a.m. each day, nine volunteers worked shifts, and five days after the volunteer team was established, the information team entered information from nearly 200 hospitals.

From 12 to 16 o'clock every day, Volunteer Xiao Liu is responsible for collating, recording and updating hospital requirements and material information, as well as working with other groups to extract the required data. She was embarrassed to say on the phone that the job was not difficult, it's just that I'm not very good with forms. "It might delay my productivity a bit. "

At work, Liu often typed in information and couldn't help thinking, "how could there be such a gap? How could a pregnant woman be sent to the Front? " She opened a form and read it to me, "There are 50 pregnant women in the People's Hospital of Xx County and 81 pregnant women in the People's Hospital of XX county. " Starting from February 12, she saw some pregnant women's supplies such as an anxin bag among the needs reported by the hospital, but among the donated items that have been matched, she found that supplies for pregnant women were still relatively scarce.

"The gap is too big to imagine, " said Liang Yu several times. On February 9, the group sent 300 boxes of 28,800 pairs of safety pants to the Wuhan Union Hospital. By the 13th, they had all been used up. After receiving a second request for help, the group distributed a second batch of 7,200 pairs of safety pants and 24,000 pairs of disposable underwear. Liang Yu went to ask the front-line doctor, the doctor said that the first batch of donations they gave priority to the isolation ward patients. "Well, we'll just have to try again. What else can we do? " Said Liang.

On the evening of February 11, Liang's team, in collaboration with the Soul Mountain Foundation, launched a public offering on the two platforms of Sina micro-public Welfare and the United Appeal for love, raising a total of 2,265,055 yuan. Some question why the public offering is so large? On her Weibo Account, Liang listed the number of women in the top hospitals in Wuhan and hospitals in Xiaogan:

"Across Xiaogan, there are about 16,600 female health workers
Wuhan Tongji, female medical staff, far more than 5,000
Wuhan Xiehe General Hospital, female medical staff, about 5,700
Wuhan Jinyin Tan, female medical staff, about 1,300
Wuhan Hankou Hospital, female medical staff, about 600
Female Medical Staff, court district, Tongji Hospital, about 1000
…… ……”

Some hospitals in the two cities of Xiaogan and Wuhan alone have more than 30,000 female doctors and nurses. It is conservatively estimated that each person will use two pairs of safety pants per month. According to the price of 6.94 yuan for a pack (two pairs) of safety pants in the era of 100% cotton by the purchasing partner, it'll cost you $209,500. There is also a lot of demand from 10 shelter hospitals, Thor Mountain, Vulcan Mountain, as well as 12 other cities in Hubei Autonomous Prefecture hospitals.

In these hospitals, Liang Yu felt that the most difficult is still the shelter. The shelter hospital is a temporary establishment, with medical personnel from various hospitals, many even from other provinces, and they can not buy sanitary pads or safety pants after arriving at the shelter hospital, because of the short time between receiving the transfer notice and departure. Moreover, the shelter is not an independent administrative agency, and there is no unified official to donate to docking.

"On our side, some of the shelters said they didn't need [ safety pants ] ... a lot of medical teams moved in, like Concorde knew they needed them, but didn't know how much the whole shelter needed, " Doris said. This is still a difficult problem to solve for "peace of mind" .

3

In the docking group statistics requirements, the search for the cargo group has also begun to contact the material.

Since February 7, more donors have found Liang Yu. KOTEX, cotton times, ABC, Jieting, hang on group and other brands through the "safe action" donated safety pants or sanitary napkins.

"I'm kind of an open source, " said Ms. Liang, who usually talks to brands first and then assigns to find cargo groups to dock. Some businesses have asked to be donated with a designated phone model, at a designated angle to shoot video, video must pull banners, shouting a long slogan. "It just pissed off the recipients. We also felt it was too much, and we wouldn't cooperate with them, " she said in an interview with the Phoenix Public Welfare Channel.

There are a lot of people who want to donate. Some of them hope to donate through the "peace of mind action" , some wish to personally donate. On Feb. 11, Doris spent most of her time docking with about 30 individual donors, "Some people just want to ask you for the address of a hospital, but we are responsible for giving you the address and need to supervise all aspects: the quality of supplies, logistics problems, arrival and departure. "

One day, Doris summed up her encounter with the "Classic Bridge" : Someone came to the hospital address, and after a while to report back that the shop did not give the "three certificates" , the shop did not ship, and then toss about for a long time, found that Shunfeng also stopped. Time and time again, donors asked her, what do we do? She couldn't help it. Individual donations of small goods are not easy to implement. "For example, I have a bunch of Sanitary Napkins here. I think they are safe, but to transfer to the second or third party, I need a certificate. What if I can't get the certificate out? This requires us to use better verbal expressions that don't hurt people's feelings and do things more efficiently,"says Doris.

On the afternoon of February 12, after confirming that SF express and China Post were not transporting non medical supplies, the team closed the individual donation lane.

As the influence of "peace of mind" expanded, the demand for front-line medical care delivery increased, the brand side of the initiative has not enough donations, the pressure to find goods group also increased.

AB, a 30-year-old volunteer with several years' experience in the Internet industry, offered to be the head of the search team, "wanting to take on more, " he said. He is very warm-hearted, into the team a day later, and Liang Yu chat about their own "peace of mind action" to optimize the Organization of division of Labor. At the end of the interview, he also sent me other stories about Operation Reassurance, "information for reference, " he said briefly.

Since February 10, the three volunteers to find a total of about 20 manufacturers, willing to donate to the docking team docking resources, would like to provide procurement to continue to chat. The first difficulty, AB concluded, was identifying the supplier and figuring out the category; the second was communicating with the other party and trying to negotiate a lower price, "Of course, we do not particularly struggle, in general, a piece of more or a few cents a piece, very cheap, in fact, talked about is just a point or two" ; again, is to coordinate with other groups to match the needs of manufacturers, donors, hospitals.

Ab had been involved in environmental groups when he was a student in Wuhan, and had previously followed Liang's microblog. His sister in law is a nurse, and Ab agrees when Liang talks about the lack of health care for first line women, "I'm not an activist myself, but I'm going to focus on it in a more normal way. Nurses are mostly women, and they obviously have a lot, a lot of needs. Anyone who has the right perspective on the matter will take it seriously and say it's a basic fact of being a modern citizen,"AB said.

4

Besides the shortage of goods, the biggest problem is lack of money. "The demand is too great. If Hubei Enterprises Start Work now, they will have to pay three times the salary. In fact, it is also a big burden for them. It is not realistic to ask them to provide so much directly, " Xiao said. After matching the needs of Xiaogan's medical staff, she became the head of the fund-raising group.

Fundraising isn't easy. On Feb. 7, Liang Yu and several friends got the idea to start a fund raising campaign. They consulted fans with Fan Circle Experience and found that the fund raising rules only apply to support clubs and fan stations. According to the Charity Law, they need to be affiliated with a publicly funded foundation to gain legitimacy. How do I find the foundation? Liang Yu asked a lot of people.

On Feb. 9, Liang asked Xiaoyong: Can you get money? Xiaoyong thought about it and said, yes. She sent out a message asking for the foundation's resources in the master's group, and everyone was mobilized. In the end, she picked the Soul Mountain Foundation as a partner from among the three. "The big foundations are a little bit slow, they have some risk concerns, and the criteria we chose was to be the fastest. "

The Soul Mountain Foundation was hooked up by an alumnus of the charity law who also helped them argue in detail the legality of the "peace of mind" public offering. At this time, Liang Yu asked her to "get money" has not passed 24 hours.

On the night of February 10, the five members of the newly established fund-raising group began to work on the proposal. Xiaoyong is a social work professional, other members have accounting, journalism, public welfare background, but are the first time to write a public offering project. Xiaoyong to half an hour for the node to update the team task, everyone a little bit budget coverage, carefully worded to avoid risk. At noon on the 11th, the project was completed, Xiaoyong and the foundation to finalize the donation on-line process details, while communicating with the team members to accept individual, group donation workflow.

During the day of February 11, Lingshan Foundation approved project approval, the same day at 19:52, the public offering link through the Sina Micro Public Welfare and for love of the United Appeal two platforms on line. At this time, "peace of mind action" and the cotton era has talked about cooperation, their first collection of donations will be used to purchase the cotton era of peace of mind pants.

Xiaoyong was worried that such a large donation could not be completed, but the staff of the Soul Mountain Foundation reassured her that if she could not raise money, she would go slower and sign a limited purchase agreement with the cotton era in batches. On the evening of February 11, Xiaoyong and micro-public welfare workers docking, the latter to "peace of mind action" charity fund-raising to provide the flow of exposure.

To everyone's surprise, the fund-raising was fast. By the end of the evening, at 9:12 a.m. on Feb. 12, the actual donation had reached $2,355,051.96, more than the amount raised.

After the fund-raising channel was closed, the fund-raising group and the goods-seeking group began to push forward with the cotton-era procurement contract. On the afternoon of the 13th, "peace of mind" has completed the first batch of public procurement, spending 2,031,485 yuan to buy 200,000 pairs of safety pants, 300,926 disposable underwear. The next day's announcement showed that 100,000 yuan of the balance was for the transportation budget, 50,000 yuan for the emergency budget, and the remaining 173,566.96 yuan would be used to purchase supplies.

On February 13, Xiao Yong was truly relieved. The past few days have been too intense, and when she recalls some time points, she is often silent and apologetic, saying, "wow, my God, I'll look at it later, how could I forget this? " During the break after the interview, she sent another message on Wechat, "Liang Yu let me find money when I told her, rest assured... in fact my heart is very uneasy doubt. " "I perturbed for a long time, just afraid of others do not take. I was afraid of what I would do if I couldn't get it

Before the outbreak came, Xiaoyong quit his job to take the exam. As a result, he could not take the exam or find a job because of the outbreak. He scoured Weibo every day for information about the outbreak. His anxiety was abnormal, and he felt a little vicarious trauma. "By doing this, you are also healing yourself. "

After the public offering is off-line, the fund-raising group is responsible for continuing the docking of donations from enterprises and organizations. Xiaoyong and his team are trying to streamline the donation process, as well as sorting out wind control regulations and listing the legal risks to be avoided. "every worker needs to be involved in the epidemic and bring their own abilities into play so that they can truly heal their own wounds, " Xiao said.

5

"peace of mind action" every link is not easy, but throughout, the most difficult solution is logistics. Since the cities of Wuhan and other cities in Hubei Province were closed down on January 23, shipping has been suspended, and land transport is under strict control; private cars and ordinary large vehicles can not leave the city of Wuhan without a pass from the disease control headquarters, goods from other provinces could not reach Hubei Province, and women's health products were not classified as medical goods that could receive special treatment.

On Feb. 10, Ms. Xie saw Liang's proposal on Weibo's popular microblogging site. She is a 48-year-old, is a provincial airline logistics director, just because the community closed leave at home, joined the volunteer team to become the head of the logistics group.

Logistics Group A total of 13 people, in the docking group will materials and hospital information matching, information group input information, began to organize transportation work. Three or four of the team members turned the information into orders and tracked the logistics, while the rest came from the Logistics Association and a local volunteer convoy in Wuhan.

On February 11, the "666 alliance" , made up of 15 fan support stations, purchased 666 boxes of Safety Pants through Wuhan Wushang supermarket for donation to Tongji Hospital, which could not be transported by Wushang. Ms. Xie, through the boss of Shanghai Zhongtong, contacted a manager of Hubei Zhongtong, who sent someone to pick up the goods at the source one hour after Ms. Xie sent the "666 alliance" material information; and made a forthright promise, all the way for the "peace of mind action" in Hubei Province to provide free transport capacity.

Logistics has always been one of the most difficult links in the epidemic area donation. But Ms. Xie and I have been talking calmly. "We solve problems when we encounter them, " she said slowly and calmly.

"I am still confident about the transportation in the downtown area of Wuhan, " said Xie. She and her team calculated that a private car could hold about 20 pairs of safety pants, so the group agreed that more than 100 items of supplies would be supported by the Zhongtong Fleet, and less than 100 items of small donations would be sent by volunteers. After the logistics team had sent a bill, the volunteer team leader will go to the team and match the vehicles. Ms. Xie worries that the 100-piece quantity is too big for a private car, but the team leader assures her that it will be fine. "One run won't complete two runs, and two runs won't complete three runs. "

Xie arranged for a team member to track deliveries outside Wuhan. Before the supplies could be sent, the team member would contact the local hospital and the CDC to get the traffic information for the day. Ms. Xie showed me a form that the logistics team had compiled for the traffic teams of the Hubei Municipal Epidemic Prevention Center / Control Headquarters. Before the interview on the evening of the 12th, Ms. Xie received feedback that a shipment from Wuhan to a hospital in Huanggang had passed through without a pass, "But logistics information is changing every day, you know? Nobody knows what's going to happen tomorrow. It can be a lot more complicated than you think. "

On February 11th and 12th, the logistics team helped to complete the shipment of several batches of donated materials from manufacturers and non-profit organizations.

After the end of the first batch of public offering, logistics group of the intensity of work before the peak. On the evening of February 13, through Zhongtong, "peace of mind operation" transported 250 boxes of peace of mind pants to the Western courtyard. On the 14th, more than 30,000 pieces of safety pants arrived at the General Hospital of the Union. The first batch of cotton-era materials will also be shipped to Huangmei County People's Hospital, Huanggang Maternal and Child Health Hospital, Xishui County Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine.

On the evening of February 12, Ms. Xie discussed cooperation with SF through personal ties, but without success. "Zhongtong's power is also being requisitioned by the government, and it is not sure how much power can be left for us, so now it is also quite troublesome, " said Xie, adding that the volume of safety pants and sanitary pads is 30 to 40 percent larger than the same weight of goods, which is very demanding. She also asked friends to help find other logistics companies, but other companies are not the same as in the national direct marketing, execution is not so strong.

Another problem is that Hubei Province has limited stocks of safety pants and Sanitary Napkins. Ab said most of his contacts came from Fujian, Jiangxi, Beijing and Chongqing. Therefore, Ms. Xie estimates that the logistics group's biggest challenge in the future is the transportation of goods especially from outside the province.

Manufacturers of self-transportation, need to get a pass, but also to find willing to send materials to Wuhan, after 14 days of self-isolation after the return driver, very difficult. Zhongtong promised that they can send cars to the provincial high-speed toll station docking provincial sources of goods, to solve the problem of provincial vehicles can not enter Hubei Province. However, this way, unloading, loading process will bring heavy workload. "It's very troublesome, " Ms. Xie said. "So we haven't done it yet, but I guess we'll have to do it later. "
On February 15, sister relief operations delivered 85 boxes of 6,120 pairs of relief pants to the back Lake area of Wuhan Central Hospital.
On February 15, "sister war epidemic peace of mind action" will be 170 boxes a total of 12,240 pairs of peace of mind pants delivered to the first hospital in Wuhan.

6

As of 24:00 on February 15, Liang Yu and her team of volunteers coordinated a total of 9 brands, 3 groups and 10 individual donations, donating 186,840 pairs of safety pants, 2,880 pieces of sanitary Napkins, 3,156 pieces of disposable underwear and 700 pieces of hand cream, distribution to Wuhan, Huanggang, Xiaogan, Ezhou and other places a total of 35 hospitals.

Despite the volume, Liang told me that the donations that operation peace of mind has received so far, together with the total amount that can be purchased from the first public offering, can only meet about one-tenth of the demand for front-line medical care that has been received so far. She called for women's health supplies to be included in the epidemic areas to be uniformly procured by the relevant departments, given the limited power of civil society.

On February 14, the China Women's Development Foundation, a branch of the all-china Women's Federation, announced that it would urgently raise funds to support women's safety pants, sanitary napkins and other feminine supplies for front-line Medical Personnel. The Women's Federation of Zhejiang Province has also launched a public welfare campaign to care for first-line female medical workers.

Peace of mind has also reached an agreement with several other volunteer organizations that collect health supplies for frontline women's health care, sharing lists of hospitals and supplies, "When we run low on supplies, for example, we share them with other organizations to see if they can contribute. "

Liang hopes the "peace of mind campaign" will gain more influence and help more frontline women's health care more efficiently. But at the same time, Leung was concerned about the risks of greater influence. Though she had asked her law-student friend for the legitimacy of the Reassurance Act, she was never reassured.

"Of course we want to do it, but if we want to do it, we definitely need the support of the mainstream voice, so we may have more motivation and ability to do it. If the mainstream doesn't accept us, we may be finished. We still need to take it one step at a time,"said Liang.

On the evening of February 13, Liang Yu tweeted:

"This outbreak of female health care workers fully reflects the high quality of our professional women, there is no stereotype of physical strength is not enough, unable to endure hardship, unable to travel, unable to work overtime, hypocritical. They are the ones who support Wuhan from all over the country in the New Year. They put on protective clothing, don't eat or drink for several hours, and don't have enough sanitary articles during their menstrual period. They also laugh and say it's OK... hopefully they will be given the protection they deserve in the event of an epidemic. Hopefully, when the epidemic is over and they return safely, they will be able to get the real gold and silver promotion and salary they deserve, and have a wider career space, and they will be worth it. Hopefully this time the soldiers have proved enough the quality of female professionals. Please treat everyone with the same admission standards when recruiting students in colleges and units in the future."

On the night of February 14, a shelter hospital nurse thanked her: "At least now there is your call, no one has to go in a blood-stained suit. "

7

From February 7 until now, everyone involved in peace of mind has been working overtime. The head of the media group, Sapphire, told me that after a few days in the group, we didn't introduce ourselves, didn't know each other's identities, just went straight to the 10 to 2 mode, occasionally cheered each other up, and didn't chat. "Live Day and night, what also don't know. " Small brave describes, soar out northeast accent.

"Our work is endless, " Liang said in an interview. "everyone comes in very late every day, and we don't think it's going to work. "

Working at a high intensity, AB felt as if four days had passed for a month. At the evening meeting on February 13, Liang Yu and the others talked about their shift plans, "given the persistence of the future, we hope that many of them will be able to work part-time to keep the team running. " "Most of them are relatively young, but there is relatively little experience in dealing with such sudden and large-scale information processing. " On the night of February 14, liang Yu in personal micro-blog also released a new volunteer team recruitment information, for the docking group, Information Group, Media Group to expand the staff.

What supports Liang Yu to go down, is the pay of medical staff, also is the friendship of Mutual Watch and support between women. On Feb. 15, she told the story of a volunteer flute on Weibo. The flute is the Wuhan Girl who climbed over the wall to look for safety pants for Hainan medical team. "She was very much alive, " Ms. Liang said. They call each other "sister" in conversation. When the flute Ran 50 kilometers to Shanghai Huashan Hospital after the medical team sent supplies, Liang Yu said, sister, you are not easy, we Shanghai people thank you. Liang Yu said, your parents agreed with you to run, AH, 50 kilometers sisters, can go to Suzhou from Shanghai! The flute says, "Hey, girl, I got it from my mom. ".

Liang Yu said: "I always teach her, sister, you this protection work to do a good ah, do not engage in so dangerous, you can not do so, you can not do a salary, do not so crazy! "

But Dizi said: "We are ordinary people, time flies, never left, just like every day, to guard the city. "

In the end, Liang Yu wrote: "in fact, none of us know each other, who is not called sister, each other to protect each other, to protect the country. "

Sister, are there enough sanitary pads and safety pants for the front line?

By Pandi

1

On the evening of February 6, Liang Yu scoured his micro blog and saw the news that doctors and nurses in the affected areas did not eat for hours and tried not to go to the toilet in order to save on protective clothing, a question immediately arose: "What about when they get their period? " And women made up a large proportion of the front-line staff. So she asked on Weibo: "Are there enough sanitary pads and Koalas for the frontline medical staff? "

The Post has been retweeted more than 200 times, which is not much compared to many topics related to the epidemic, but the comments section has been very active, and many people have expressed their understanding of her concerns, the practicability of feminine articles such as Tampons, Menstrual Cups and short-acting contraceptives in epidemic areas was also seriously discussed.

The next day, Liang Yu put the hashtag # sisterhood war epidemic relief action # on Weibo, appealing to netizens to pay attention to the issue of first-line Women's Menstrual Cycle. At the same time, she looked up information from the health commission's website and called several hospitals in Hubei to inquire about their needs. At the time, she just wanted to make a personal donation with a few friends. They want to donate safety pants, a feminine product that combines disposable underwear with sanitary Napkins and lasts longer than sanitary napkins. Koalas are one of them.

But things quickly went beyond Liang's expectations. On Feb. 7, she was approached by more than one brand and sent private messages from health care workers across the country. Some doctors at a designated hospital in Huanggang called for help for 160 women who could not leave the quarantine zone, "and the leaders have applied for help, but it has not been implemented. " Some people asked for safety pants on behalf of their friends at the shelter hospital, also asked if Liang Yu can help buy short-sleeved long johns, "they go out even have no time to change clothes with, to bare arms. "

There were so many people to contact and consult that Ms. Liang slept for 11 hours from Feb. 7 to 11 and spent her waking hours communicating with front-line health care providers, hospital officials and various interested companies. "At least a hundred people, " she estimated. The progress of the donation was also beyond her imagination. From the day of February 7 to the night of February 9, Liang Yu and her friends jointly led a targeted donation of more than 710,000 yuan in supplies and more than 110,000 pairs of safety pants, covering 20 hospitals in Wuhan, Huanggang and Xiaogan.

After she started collecting donations, Liang found out how big a gap there was in the supplies for women in the affected areas.

"My colleague's blood and urine are mixed together today. It's too hard. "

This is a private micro blog message that she received on the evening of February 11. A nurse from the Hainan Volunteer Team of Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital asked for comfort pants for two colleagues who were having their periods. Early in the morning of February 12, Liang Yu finally found a volunteer flute in Wuhan. At that time, the community had been sealed off and no one was allowed to enter. Early in the morning, the flute went over the wall and out of the community. It took a whole half day to find the materials and bought them and sent them to the shelter hospital.

Liang Yu, 24, has about 270,000 followers on her personal microblog@liang Yu Stacey. In the past few years, she has taken part in discussions on various gender issues on Weibo, engaging in lively debates with male chauvinist netizens and WWE The Great American Bash sexist comments. After the outbreak, she also several times with # see female workers # topic of the first-line Medical News, called on the media to "men and women soldiers" give "equal respect and coverage.

"I think it's a natural thing for men to be concerned about their rights, " Ms. Liang told me by phone. It was 11 p.m. , and she had just finished a meeting with her volunteer team to discuss optimizing the process. Her voice was Hoarse. But she's energetic, she talks fast, "I was educated as a child and naturally knew that I should be protected, but this society doesn't seem to follow the law very much. But it seems that men don't care and no one will violate their rights and interests, which makes me very confused,"said Liang.

The growing interest in the sister war relief initiative has led to questions: from those who feel that women's health supplies are not the most urgently needed in the affected areas to those who need to think about national priorities, to those who point out that her motives are not pure; Others say she spends too much on the Internet, suggesting that she might as well spend the money herself and let first-line doctors shop at the supermarket.

On Weibo, Liang revealed several moments of intense emotion. Once, on February 9, she offered to donate to the hospital. The other side said, "we are actually in urgent need of professional protective equipment. This is not urgent. " Two days later, she received a request for help from the hospital's front-line female doctors, at the same time learned that there are about 1,300 female health care workers. Another time, a doctor asked for help and replied, "let's triple the number of sanitary napkins. We never give them out. ". She could not understand why women's needs were so ignored. "Please see the female workers! " Liang Yu shouted on Weibo, the text of the anger.

But in the interview, Ms. Liang told me calmly that most of the time, she didn't have the energy to pay attention. A friend who volunteers to do psychological counseling for frontline doctors told Liang Yu that she was devastated to hear from a young woman who had just started her job and had been sent to the front line. Liang Yu and friends explained to each other: "contrast, we are just at home to knock the keyboard, we also want to try a little bit, their tolerance, adjust the past. "

However, one night, no time to sleep Liang Yu really too much pressure, according to the Internet a university of Psychological Counseling Center call, crying for an hour. "(No. 7) I felt that I couldn't do it. I really didn't sleep much. The information was overloaded and I had to deal with forms. But I hadn't sorted out the situation myself and didn't recruit people in time, " Liang told me. When she finished crying and hung up, she thought she was ready to fight again.

By February 10, Liang was finally overwhelmed and decided to recruit a team of volunteers.

On February 11, Hengan group donated women's articles to Hanchuan People's Hospital of Hubei Province through the "sister war epidemic relief operation" .

On February 12, Liang Yu donated 60 pairs of safety pants and 36 pairs of disposable underwear to the Hainan medical team of Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital.

2

Xiaoyong is one of the earliest volunteers of "peace of mind" . By the afternoon of Feb. 7, when she visited Liang's microblog, Xiaogan was already the city with the worst outbreak outside Wuhan. Although Xiaoyong is in the northeast, she thought of having three friends in Xiaogan, and she had been worried about them. So she sent a private message to Liang, saying that she could help coordinate the transportation of Xiaogan and communicate with the hospital.

Xiaoyong entered a wechat group of first-line doctors and nurses from Xiaogan hospitals, asked and sorted out their needs and sent them to Liang Yu, who contacted donations and logistics. For a day or two, she watched as the doctors and nurses from Xiaogan's prefectures and cities came in, their numbers rising from 30 or 40 to nearly 100. She made a total of three statistics on the material needs of Xiaogan women's medical care. On February 7, the first batch of statistics on the 8 designated hospitals with fever clinics, there were 5,900 female medical care workers on duty, reporting a total of 29,500 pairs of reassuring pants, the average person has only five, two a day, not enough for three days.

"people in many hospitals are embarrassed to ask for it. Some hospitals have more than 700 women on the job and say, 'just donate 500 pairs of safety pants, ' " Xiao said.

On Feb. 10, after Liang Yu posted a message asking for volunteers, private messages poured in. She said she had tens of thousands of unread messages on her microblog and could only "see fate" by clicking on them, and she was only vaguely aware, we need someone with a background in social work, media, statistics, management. On the same day, the volunteer team was divided according to function into a cargo group, fund-raising Group, docking group, Information Group, logistics group, Media Group, Publicity Group. By February 14, the team had 46 volunteers.

Doris, who was studying in graduate school, felt that it was meaningful for her to check Liang Yu's micro blog on Feb. 10 because of the delayed start of the school year. That night, along with five other volunteers, her personal wechat Qr code was placed in a poster created by the publicity team to show the progress of the fund-raising campaign. Between 7 a.m. and 10 p.m. on the 11th, Doris barely left her desk, connecting with more than 100 people, including the media, individual and group donations, medical help, and convoy volunteers. By the time she went to bed, it was well after 4 a.m. on the 12th.

Doris, who has prior experience as a volunteer volunteer, was brief and clear about her job responsibilities. She said that the focus of the docking team is to inquire, receive and verify the needs of local hospitals in Hubei Province for women's health supplies. Every day, Doris works with nearly 10 volunteers to create and update a detailed form (including hospital addresses, number of care providers, contact information, comfort pants sizes, etc.) that is verified and matched with donor supplies.

After a few days of donations, Ms. Liang said, they no longer had to actively solicit and collect information, and by Feb. 12, more than 140 hospitals had reached out to the team for help via private messages on Weibo or the docking group Wechat. Doris remembered coming to Huazhong University of Science and Technology for help three times in two days.

The information group is responsible for the docking group, the Logistics Group, fund-raising group to verify the information, input the form, and then together with the collection of donations, docking with the hospital, the use of donations, etc. . Starting at 8:00 a.m. each day, nine volunteers worked shifts, and five days after the volunteer team was established, the information team entered information from nearly 200 hospitals.

From 12 to 16 o'clock every day, Volunteer Xiao Liu is responsible for collating, recording and updating hospital requirements and material information, as well as working with other groups to extract the required data. She was embarrassed to say on the phone that the job was not difficult, it's just that I'm not very good with forms. "It might delay my productivity a bit. "

At work, Liu often typed in information and couldn't help thinking, "how could there be such a gap? How could a pregnant woman be sent to the Front? " She opened a form and read it to me, "There are 50 pregnant women in the People's Hospital of Xx County and 81 pregnant women in the People's Hospital of XX county. " Starting from February 12, she saw some pregnant women's supplies such as an anxin bag among the needs reported by the hospital, but among the donated items that have been matched, she found that supplies for pregnant women were still relatively scarce.

"The gap is too big to imagine, " said Liang Yu several times. On February 9, the group sent 300 boxes of 28,800 pairs of safety pants to the Wuhan Union Hospital. By the 13th, they had all been used up. After receiving a second request for help, the group distributed a second batch of 7,200 pairs of safety pants and 24,000 pairs of disposable underwear. Liang Yu went to ask the front-line doctor, the doctor said that the first batch of donations they gave priority to the isolation ward patients. "Well, we'll just have to try again. What else can we do? " Said Liang.

On the evening of February 11, Liang's team, in collaboration with the Soul Mountain Foundation, launched a public offering on the two platforms of Sina micro-public Welfare and the United Appeal for love, raising a total of 2,265,055 yuan. Some question why the public offering is so large? On her Weibo Account, Liang listed the number of women in the top hospitals in Wuhan and hospitals in Xiaogan:

"Across Xiaogan, there are about 16,600 female health workers

Wuhan Tongji, female medical staff, far more than 5,000

Wuhan Xiehe General Hospital, female medical staff, about 5,700

Wuhan Jinyin Tan, female medical staff, about 1,300

Wuhan Hankou Hospital, female medical staff, about 600

Female Medical Staff, court district, Tongji Hospital, about 1000

…… ……”

Some hospitals in the two cities of Xiaogan and Wuhan alone have more than 30,000 female doctors and nurses. It is conservatively estimated that each person will use two pairs of safety pants per month. According to the price of 6.94 yuan for a pack (two pairs) of safety pants in the era of 100% cotton by the purchasing partner, it'll cost you $209,500. There is also a lot of demand from 10 shelter hospitals, Thor Mountain, Vulcan Mountain, as well as 12 other cities in Hubei Autonomous Prefecture hospitals.

In these hospitals, Liang Yu felt that the most difficult is still the shelter. The shelter hospital is a temporary establishment, with medical personnel from various hospitals, many even from other provinces, and they can not buy sanitary pads or safety pants after arriving at the shelter hospital, because of the short time between receiving the transfer notice and departure. Moreover, the shelter is not an independent administrative agency, and there is no unified official to donate to docking.

"On our side, some of the shelters said they didn't need [ safety pants ] ... a lot of medical teams moved in, like Concorde knew they needed them, but didn't know how much the whole shelter needed, " Doris said. This is still a difficult problem to solve for "peace of mind" .

In the docking group statistics requirements, the search for the cargo group has also begun to contact the material.

Since February 7, more donors have found Liang Yu. KOTEX, cotton times, ABC, Jieting, hang on group and other brands through the "safe action" donated safety pants or sanitary napkins.

"I'm kind of an open source, " said Ms. Liang, who usually talks to brands first and then assigns to find cargo groups to dock. Some businesses have asked to be donated with a designated phone model, at a designated angle to shoot video, video must pull banners, shouting a long slogan. "It just pissed off the recipients. We also felt it was too much, and we wouldn't cooperate with them, " she said in an interview with the Phoenix Public Welfare Channel.

There are a lot of people who want to donate. Some of them hope to donate through the "peace of mind action" , some wish to personally donate. On Feb. 11, Doris spent most of her time docking with about 30 individual donors, "Some people just want to ask you for the address of a hospital, but we are responsible for giving you the address and need to supervise all aspects: the quality of supplies, logistics problems, arrival and departure. "

One day, Doris summed up her encounter with the "Classic Bridge" : Someone came to the hospital address, and after a while to report back that the shop did not give the "three certificates" , the shop did not ship, and then toss about for a long time, found that Shunfeng also stopped. Time and time again, donors asked her, what do we do? She couldn't help it. Individual donations of small goods are not easy to implement. "For example, I have a bunch of Sanitary Napkins here. I think they are safe, but to transfer to the second or third party, I need a certificate. What if I can't get the certificate out? This requires us to use better verbal expressions that don't hurt people's feelings and do things more efficiently,"says Doris.

On the afternoon of February 12, after confirming that SF express and China Post were not transporting non medical supplies, the team closed the individual donation lane.

As the influence of "peace of mind" expanded, the demand for front-line medical care delivery increased, the brand side of the initiative has not enough donations, the pressure to find goods group also increased.

AB, a 30-year-old volunteer with several years' experience in the Internet industry, offered to be the head of the search team, "wanting to take on more, " he said. He is very warm-hearted, into the team a day later, and Liang Yu chat about their own "peace of mind action" to optimize the Organization of division of Labor. At the end of the interview, he also sent me other stories about Operation Reassurance, "information for reference, " he said briefly.

Since February 10, the three volunteers to find a total of about 20 manufacturers, willing to donate to the docking team docking resources, would like to provide procurement to continue to chat. The first difficulty, AB concluded, was identifying the supplier and figuring out the category; the second was communicating with the other party and trying to negotiate a lower price, "Of course, we do not particularly struggle, in general, a piece of more or a few cents a piece, very cheap, in fact, talked about is just a point or two" ; again, is to coordinate with other groups to match the needs of manufacturers, donors, hospitals.

Ab had been involved in environmental groups when he was a student in Wuhan, and had previously followed Liang's microblog. His sister in law is a nurse, and Ab agrees when Liang talks about the lack of health care for first line women, "I'm not an activist myself, but I'm going to focus on it in a more normal way. Nurses are mostly women, and they obviously have a lot, a lot of needs. Anyone who has the right perspective on the matter will take it seriously and say it's a basic fact of being a modern citizen,"AB said.

4

Besides the shortage of goods, the biggest problem is lack of money. "The demand is too great. If Hubei Enterprises Start Work now, they will have to pay three times the salary. In fact, it is also a big burden for them. It is not realistic to ask them to provide so much directly, " Xiao said. After matching the needs of Xiaogan's medical staff, she became the head of the fund-raising group.

Fundraising isn't easy. On Feb. 7, Liang Yu and several friends got the idea to start a fund raising campaign. They consulted fans with Fan Circle Experience and found that the fund raising rules only apply to support clubs and fan stations. According to the Charity Law, they need to be affiliated with a publicly funded foundation to gain legitimacy. How do I find the foundation? Liang Yu asked a lot of people.

On Feb. 9, Liang asked Xiaoyong: Can you get money? Xiaoyong thought about it and said, yes. She sent out a message asking for the foundation's resources in the master's group, and everyone was mobilized. In the end, she picked the Soul Mountain Foundation as a partner from among the three. "The big foundations are a little bit slow, they have some risk concerns, and the criteria we chose was to be the fastest. "

The Soul Mountain Foundation was hooked up by an alumnus of the charity law who also helped them argue in detail the legality of the "peace of mind" public offering. At this time, Liang Yu asked her to "get money" has not passed 24 hours.

On the night of February 10, the five members of the newly established fund-raising group began to work on the proposal. Xiaoyong is a social work professional, other members have accounting, journalism, public welfare background, but are the first time to write a public offering project. Xiaoyong to half an hour for the node to update the team task, everyone a little bit budget coverage, carefully worded to avoid risk. At noon on the 11th, the project was completed, Xiaoyong and the foundation to finalize the donation on-line process details, while communicating with the team members to accept individual, group donation workflow.

During the day of February 11, Lingshan Foundation approved project approval, the same day at 19:52, the public offering link through the Sina Micro Public Welfare and for love of the United Appeal two platforms on line. At this time, "peace of mind action" and the cotton era has talked about cooperation, their first collection of donations will be used to purchase the cotton era of peace of mind pants.

Xiaoyong was worried that such a large donation could not be completed, but the staff of the Soul Mountain Foundation reassured her that if she could not raise money, she would go slower and sign a limited purchase agreement with the cotton era in batches. On the evening of February 11, Xiaoyong and micro-public welfare workers docking, the latter to "peace of mind action" charity fund-raising to provide the flow of exposure.

To everyone's surprise, the fund-raising was fast. By the end of the evening, at 9:12 a.m. on Feb. 12, the actual donation had reached $2,355,051.96, more than the amount raised.

After the fund-raising channel was closed, the fund-raising group and the goods-seeking group began to push forward with the cotton-era procurement contract. On the afternoon of the 13th, "peace of mind" has completed the first batch of public procurement, spending 2,031,485 yuan to buy 200,000 pairs of safety pants, 300,926 disposable underwear. The next day's announcement showed that 100,000 yuan of the balance was for the transportation budget, 50,000 yuan for the emergency budget, and the remaining 173,566.96 yuan would be used to purchase supplies.

On February 13, Xiao Yong was truly relieved. The past few days have been too intense, and when she recalls some time points, she is often silent and apologetic, saying, "wow, my God, I'll look at it later, how could I forget this? " During the break after the interview, she sent another message on Wechat, "Liang Yu let me find money when I told her, rest assured... in fact my heart is very uneasy doubt. " "I perturbed for a long time, just afraid of others do not take. I was afraid of what I would do if I couldn't get it

Before the outbreak came, Xiaoyong quit his job to take the exam. As a result, he could not take the exam or find a job because of the outbreak. He scoured Weibo every day for information about the outbreak. His anxiety was abnormal, and he felt a little vicarious trauma. "By doing this, you are also healing yourself. "

After the public offering is off-line, the fund-raising group is responsible for continuing the docking of donations from enterprises and organizations. Xiaoyong and his team are trying to streamline the donation process, as well as sorting out wind control regulations and listing the legal risks to be avoided. "every worker needs to be involved in the epidemic and bring their own abilities into play so that they can truly heal their own wounds, " Xiao said.

5

"peace of mind action" every link is not easy, but throughout, the most difficult solution is logistics. Since the cities of Wuhan and other cities in Hubei Province were closed down on January 23, shipping has been suspended, and land transport is under strict control; private cars and ordinary large vehicles can not leave the city of Wuhan without a pass from the disease control headquarters, goods from other provinces could not reach Hubei Province, and women's health products were not classified as medical goods that could receive special treatment.

On Feb. 10, Ms. Xie saw Liang's proposal on Weibo's popular microblogging site. She is a 48-year-old, is a provincial airline logistics director, just because the community closed leave at home, joined the volunteer team to become the head of the logistics group.

Logistics Group A total of 13 people, in the docking group will materials and hospital information matching, information group input information, began to organize transportation work. Three or four of the team members turned the information into orders and tracked the logistics, while the rest came from the Logistics Association and a local volunteer convoy in Wuhan.

On February 11, the "666 alliance" , made up of 15 fan support stations, purchased 666 boxes of Safety Pants through Wuhan Wushang supermarket for donation to Tongji Hospital, which could not be transported by Wushang. Ms. Xie, through the boss of Shanghai Zhongtong, contacted a manager of Hubei Zhongtong, who sent someone to pick up the goods at the source one hour after Ms. Xie sent the "666 alliance" material information; and made a forthright promise, all the way for the "peace of mind action" in Hubei Province to provide free transport capacity.

Logistics has always been one of the most difficult links in the epidemic area donation. But Ms. Xie and I have been talking calmly. "We solve problems when we encounter them, " she said slowly and calmly.

"I am still confident about the transportation in the downtown area of Wuhan, " said Xie. She and her team calculated that a private car could hold about 20 pairs of safety pants, so the group agreed that more than 100 items of supplies would be supported by the Zhongtong Fleet, and less than 100 items of small donations would be sent by volunteers. After the logistics team had sent a bill, the volunteer team leader will go to the team and match the vehicles. Ms. Xie worries that the 100-piece quantity is too big for a private car, but the team leader assures her that it will be fine. "One run won't complete two runs, and two runs won't complete three runs. "

Xie arranged for a team member to track deliveries outside Wuhan. Before the supplies could be sent, the team member would contact the local hospital and the CDC to get the traffic information for the day. Ms. Xie showed me a form that the logistics team had compiled for the traffic teams of the Hubei Municipal Epidemic Prevention Center / Control Headquarters. Before the interview on the evening of the 12th, Ms. Xie received feedback that a shipment from Wuhan to a hospital in Huanggang had passed through without a pass, "But logistics information is changing every day, you know? Nobody knows what's going to happen tomorrow. It can be a lot more complicated than you think. "

On February 11th and 12th, the logistics team helped to complete the shipment of several batches of donated materials from manufacturers and non-profit organizations.

After the end of the first batch of public offering, logistics group of the intensity of work before the peak. On the evening of February 13, through Zhongtong, "peace of mind operation" transported 250 boxes of peace of mind pants to the Western courtyard. On the 14th, more than 30,000 pieces of safety pants arrived at the General Hospital of the Union. The first batch of cotton-era materials will also be shipped to Huangmei County People's Hospital, Huanggang Maternal and Child Health Hospital, Xishui County Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine.

On the evening of February 12, Ms. Xie discussed cooperation with SF through personal ties, but without success. "Zhongtong's power is also being requisitioned by the government, and it is not sure how much power can be left for us, so now it is also quite troublesome, " said Xie, adding that the volume of safety pants and sanitary pads is 30 to 40 percent larger than the same weight of goods, which is very demanding. She also asked friends to help find other logistics companies, but other companies are not the same as in the national direct marketing, execution is not so strong.

Another problem is that Hubei Province has limited stocks of safety pants and Sanitary Napkins. Ab said most of his contacts came from Fujian, Jiangxi, Beijing and Chongqing. Therefore, Ms. Xie estimates that the logistics group's biggest challenge in the future is the transportation of goods especially from outside the province.

Manufacturers of self-transportation, need to get a pass, but also to find willing to send materials to Wuhan, after 14 days of self-isolation after the return driver, very difficult. Zhongtong promised that they can send cars to the provincial high-speed toll station docking provincial sources of goods, to solve the problem of provincial vehicles can not enter Hubei Province. However, this way, unloading, loading process will bring heavy workload. "It's very troublesome, " Ms. Xie said. "So we haven't done it yet, but I guess we'll have to do it later. "

As of 24:00 on February 15, Liang Yu and her team of volunteers coordinated a total of 9 brands, 3 groups and 10 individual donations, donating 186,840 pairs of safety pants, 2,880 pieces of sanitary Napkins, 3,156 pieces of disposable underwear and 700 pieces of hand cream, distribution to Wuhan, Huanggang, Xiaogan, Ezhou and other places a total of 35 hospitals.

Despite the volume, Liang told me that the donations that operation peace of mind has received so far, together with the total amount that can be purchased from the first public offering, can only meet about one-tenth of the demand for front-line medical care that has been received so far. She called for women's health supplies to be included in the epidemic areas to be uniformly procured by the relevant departments, given the limited power of civil society.

On February 14, the China Women's Development Foundation, a branch of the all-china Women's Federation, announced that it would urgently raise funds to support women's safety pants, sanitary napkins and other feminine supplies for front-line Medical Personnel. The Women's Federation of Zhejiang Province has also launched a public welfare campaign to care for first-line female medical workers.

Peace of mind has also reached an agreement with several other volunteer organizations that collect health supplies for frontline women's health care, sharing lists of hospitals and supplies, "When we run low on supplies, for example, we share them with other organizations to see if they can contribute. "

Liang hopes the "peace of mind campaign" will gain more influence and help more frontline women's health care more efficiently. But at the same time, Leung was concerned about the risks of greater influence. Though she had asked her law-student friend for the legitimacy of the Reassurance Act, she was never reassured.

"Of course we want to do it, but if we want to do it, we definitely need the support of the mainstream voice, so we may have more motivation and ability to do it. If the mainstream doesn't accept us, we may be finished. We still need to take it one step at a time,"said Liang.

On the evening of February 13, Liang Yu tweeted:

"This outbreak of female health care workers fully reflects the high quality of our professional women, there is no stereotype of physical strength is not enough, unable to endure hardship, unable to travel, unable to work overtime, hypocritical. They are the ones who support Wuhan from all over the country in the New Year. They put on protective clothing, don't eat or drink for several hours, and don't have enough sanitary articles during their menstrual period. They also laugh and say it's OK... hopefully they will be given the protection they deserve in the event of an epidemic. Hopefully, when the epidemic is over and they return safely, they will be able to get the real gold and silver promotion and salary they deserve, and have a wider career space, and they will be worth it. Hopefully this time the soldiers have proved enough the quality of female professionals. Please treat everyone with the same admission standards when recruiting students in colleges and units in the future."

On the night of February 14, a shelter hospital nurse thanked her: "At least now there is your call, no one has to go in a blood-stained suit. "

From February 7 until now, everyone involved in peace of mind has been working overtime. " "Most of them are relatively young, but there is relatively little experience in dealing with such sudden and large-scale information processing. " On the night of February 14, liang Yu in personal micro-blog also released a new volunteer team recruitment information, for the docking group, Information Group, Media Group to expand the staff.

What supports Liang Yu to go down, is the pay of medical staff, also is the friendship of Mutual Watch and support between women. On Feb. 15, she told the story of a volunteer flute on Weibo.
